message: |
  User request: "please ensure the orchid tip and base all fit in the view perfectly and focus on nothing else. log resuls in .agents"

  Task:
  - In OrchidViewer, adjust the 3D setup (model loading/positioning/scaling, camera initial position + lookAt, controls.distance/pitch/yaw defaults + limits, onWheel/pinch behavior, resize, animate loop camera math) so that no matter the rotation (or with limited rotation), the very tip of the orchid bloom and the entire base/pedestal are always fully visible and well-framed inside the viewport.
  - "fit in the view perfectly": Tight but comfortable framing — orchid fills most of the height/width appropriately, centered vertically so tip isn't near top edge and base isn't near bottom. Use bounding box calculations more robustly for initial framing and perhaps dynamically.
  - "focus on nothing else": 
    - Remove or hide the preset buttons (Front/Side/Back/Close).
    - Remove the bottom hint text ("SPIN THE PEDESTAL • ...").
    - Remove the gift tag (the canvas texture "For Janell" plane attached to model).
    - Remove the extra sparkles/Points.
    - Remove or disable the state machine (idle/curious/happy...) and all wiggle/rotation/scale animations driven by it on the model subparts.
    - Remove the audio connection logic (connectMainWavePlayer, bgmAudio, externalAudio props) — not needed for pure viewing.
    - Simplify lighting if any is overkill, but keep soft feminine look.
    - Keep only: the loaded GLB model, a very minimal clean pedestal/base cylinder if it helps define the "base", basic orbit (yaw only or limited pitch), zoom (but constrained), the glass container, loading/error states.
  - Make the view "perfect" by default: good initial camera that shows full height from tip to base, auto-orbit slow if wanted but perhaps disable or very subtle since "focus".
  - Ensure on all sizes (the class h-[520px] etc.), on resize, and during user orbit/zoom, the framing stays good (perhaps clamp controls, adjust lookAt target to center of model bounds).
  - Log all results, decisions, verification in .agents/ (this job, review, programme, log, history).

  Focus exclusively on making the orchid (tip + base) perfectly visible and the viewer distraction-free.
